Thanks @maks-a.

@rmlarsen , I would also like to note that I haven’t described in the article all the fragments that the analyzer considered to be suspicious. There were other warnings that I haven’t noted down. For example, V730 warning, that I mentioned in the article. I didn’t include such warnings in the article, because I am not very familiar with the code and it’s hard to say if the code contains an error, or if was written intentionally.

In any case it might be interesting for you to check the code yourself and have a look at the log. You can contact us by e-mail (support@viva64.com) to get a temporary license key.
